						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in Dammarguḍḍe, about a mile to the north of the Subrahmanya temple.</p>						

						<p>Vira Sōyidēva, 1324-25 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The badly damaged record seems to register a gift of money and land the king to god Kōṭiśvaradēva. It refers to mahāpradhāna Sōvaṇṇa and <hi rend="italic">senabōva</hi> Singaṇṇa-sāhaṇi.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 12[46], Raktākshi,</hi> the other details being lost. The year corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1324-25 A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
